985. Vnitr Lek. 2021 Winter;67(7):399-403.

Metabolic and endocrine diseases - is our approach always rational?

[Article in English]

Brunerová L, Urbanová J, Brož J.

Choosing wisely in metabolic and endocrine diseases shows the inutility of some, 
in clinical practice often used, ways of management. In diabetology, the routine 
recommendation for selfmonitoring of type 2 diabetic patients not treated with 
insulin represents a contraversial issue. On the contrary, there is a consensus 
on rational targets of glycemic control in elderly frailty patients with limited 
life expectancy. In endocrinology (thyroid diseases), the iniciative fights 
against the overuse of some laboratory examinations and ultrasonography. The 
recommendations on the rational indications of densitometry are discussed. In 
conclusion, these recommendations within Choosing wisely initiative of different 
professional associations usualy arise from expert views, supported by relevant 
clinical studies. They represent a challange to think over rational management 
of care.

